Firewall Configuration – Migration Runbook

Overview

As part of the migration, firewall rules were requested and configured to enable secure communication between VDI, Web Application, and Database layers.
	•	Firewall Request Reference: FWFR for AERO #77013
	•	Request Date: March 27, 2026

⸻

Configured Firewall Rules

1. VDI to Web Application VPC
	•	Source: VDI
	•	Destination: WebApp VPC
	•	Port: 443 (HTTPS)
	•	Purpose: Secure access to web application

⸻

2. VDI to Database VPC
	•	Source: VDI
	•	Destination: DB VPC
	•	Port: 1521 (Oracle DB)
	•	Purpose: Direct database connectivity (if required for admin/tools)

⸻

3. VDI to Web Application (SSH Access)
	•	Source: VDI
	•	Destination: WebApp Servers
	•	Port: 22 (SSH)
	•	Purpose: Administrative access to application servers

⸻

4. Web Application to Database
	•	Source: WebApp VPC
	•	Destination: DB VPC
	•	Port: 1521 (Oracle DB)
	•	Purpose: Application to database communication
